25/03/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Former Prime Minister Ivica Racan, the former leader of the main opposition Social Democratic Party (SDP), was rushed to hospital for surgery in Zagreb on Saturday (March 24th) after a medical complication, according to an announcement from SDP. 
Racan will remain there to continue treatment. 
He left politics several weeks ago after a cancer diagnosis, and more recently underwent surgery abroad. 
(Vecernji list - 25/03/07; Index.hr, HRT - 24/03/07)
